<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[173,1129,590,900]" box="[234,840,590,612]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Body length (mm): 1.58 (
<typeStatus box="[495,593,590,612]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">holotype</typeStatus>
), 1.66–1.81 (
<typeStatus box="[720,829,590,612]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">paratypes</typeStatus>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[173,1129,590,900]" box="[234,916,619,641]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Frons without longitudinal stripes. Thorax contrastingly yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[173,1129,590,900]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis box="[234,380,648,669]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Larger blunt black thorns/pegs of ventro-medial process of synsternite are unarranged (
<figureCitation box="[354,471,677,699]" captionStart="Figs 21–29" captionStartId="10.[136,181,1360,1382]" captionTargetBox="[140,1067,193,1332]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[136,1071,189,1338]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 21–29. Bentrovata flavithorax sp. n., male and female paratypes, postabdomen and genitalia. 21–27: male: 21 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 22 = ventromedial part of synsternite, ventral view; 23 = pseudocerci and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 24 = synsternite, anterior view; 25 = hypandrium, ventral view; 26 = surstylus, broadest (sublateral-subventral) view; 27 = postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. 28–29: female: 28 = spermathecae; 29 = cerci, dorsal view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 24; 0.2 mm for Fig. 21; 0.1 mm for Figs 22–23, 25–29" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946037/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Figs 21–22</figureCitation>
). Dorsal part of synsternite short (
<figureCitation box="[843,918,677,699]" captionStart="Figs 21–29" captionStartId="10.[136,181,1360,1382]" captionTargetBox="[140,1067,193,1332]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[136,1071,189,1338]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 21–29. Bentrovata flavithorax sp. n., male and female paratypes, postabdomen and genitalia. 21–27: male: 21 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 22 = ventromedial part of synsternite, ventral view; 23 = pseudocerci and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 24 = synsternite, anterior view; 25 = hypandrium, ventral view; 26 = surstylus, broadest (sublateral-subventral) view; 27 = postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. 28–29: female: 28 = spermathecae; 29 = cerci, dorsal view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 24; 0.2 mm for Fig. 21; 0.1 mm for Figs 22–23, 25–29" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946037/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). Pseudocerci large (
<figureCitation box="[183,259,705,728]" captionStart="Figs 21–29" captionStartId="10.[136,181,1360,1382]" captionTargetBox="[140,1067,193,1332]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[136,1071,189,1338]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 21–29. Bentrovata flavithorax sp. n., male and female paratypes, postabdomen and genitalia. 21–27: male: 21 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 22 = ventromedial part of synsternite, ventral view; 23 = pseudocerci and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 24 = synsternite, anterior view; 25 = hypandrium, ventral view; 26 = surstylus, broadest (sublateral-subventral) view; 27 = postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. 28–29: female: 28 = spermathecae; 29 = cerci, dorsal view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 24; 0.2 mm for Fig. 21; 0.1 mm for Figs 22–23, 25–29" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946037/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium Y-shaped, with long apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[769,845,705,727]" captionStart="Figs 21–29" captionStartId="10.[136,181,1360,1382]" captionTargetBox="[140,1067,193,1332]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[136,1071,189,1338]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 21–29. Bentrovata flavithorax sp. n., male and female paratypes, postabdomen and genitalia. 21–27: male: 21 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 22 = ventromedial part of synsternite, ventral view; 23 = pseudocerci and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 24 = synsternite, anterior view; 25 = hypandrium, ventral view; 26 = surstylus, broadest (sublateral-subventral) view; 27 = postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. 28–29: female: 28 = spermathecae; 29 = cerci, dorsal view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 24; 0.2 mm for Fig. 21; 0.1 mm for Figs 22–23, 25–29" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946037/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Surstylus (
<figureCitation box="[979,1052,705,727]" captionStart="Figs 21–29" captionStartId="10.[136,181,1360,1382]" captionTargetBox="[140,1067,193,1332]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[136,1071,189,1338]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 21–29. Bentrovata flavithorax sp. n., male and female paratypes, postabdomen and genitalia. 21–27: male: 21 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 22 = ventromedial part of synsternite, ventral view; 23 = pseudocerci and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 24 = synsternite, anterior view; 25 = hypandrium, ventral view; 26 = surstylus, broadest (sublateral-subventral) view; 27 = postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. 28–29: female: 28 = spermathecae; 29 = cerci, dorsal view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 24; 0.2 mm for Fig. 21; 0.1 mm for Figs 22–23, 25–29" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946037/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) short, with an extremely large black thorn ventrally. Distiphallus (
<figureCitation box="[820,892,734,756]" captionStart="Figs 21–29" captionStartId="10.[136,181,1360,1382]" captionTargetBox="[140,1067,193,1332]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[136,1071,189,1338]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 21–29. Bentrovata flavithorax sp. n., male and female paratypes, postabdomen and genitalia. 21–27: male: 21 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 22 = ventromedial part of synsternite, ventral view; 23 = pseudocerci and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 24 = synsternite, anterior view; 25 = hypandrium, ventral view; 26 = surstylus, broadest (sublateral-subventral) view; 27 = postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. 28–29: female: 28 = spermathecae; 29 = cerci, dorsal view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 24; 0.2 mm for Fig. 21; 0.1 mm for Figs 22–23, 25–29" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946037/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) rather short; postgonite long and narrow, with a proclinate, nearly sharp apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[173,1129,590,900]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis box="[234,401,792,813]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Abdomen at broadest 
<quantity box="[648,742,792,814]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.60 mm</quantity>
. Length of tergites 3–5 (mm): 0.225, 0.36, 0.225. Length/width of sternites 3–6 (mm): 0.12×0.67, 0.17×0.68, 0.12×0.66, 0.09×0.41. Epiproct membranous, without setae (
<figureCitation box="[584,658,849,872]" captionStart="Figs 21–29" captionStartId="10.[136,181,1360,1382]" captionTargetBox="[140,1067,193,1332]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[136,1071,189,1338]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 21–29. Bentrovata flavithorax sp. n., male and female paratypes, postabdomen and genitalia. 21–27: male: 21 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 22 = ventromedial part of synsternite, ventral view; 23 = pseudocerci and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 24 = synsternite, anterior view; 25 = hypandrium, ventral view; 26 = surstylus, broadest (sublateral-subventral) view; 27 = postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. 28–29: female: 28 = spermathecae; 29 = cerci, dorsal view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 24; 0.2 mm for Fig. 21; 0.1 mm for Figs 22–23, 25–29" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946037/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
). Spermathecae long ovoid (
<figureCitation box="[960,1034,849,872]" captionStart="Figs 21–29" captionStartId="10.[136,181,1360,1382]" captionTargetBox="[140,1067,193,1332]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[136,1071,189,1338]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 21–29. Bentrovata flavithorax sp. n., male and female paratypes, postabdomen and genitalia. 21–27: male: 21 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 22 = ventromedial part of synsternite, ventral view; 23 = pseudocerci and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 24 = synsternite, anterior view; 25 = hypandrium, ventral view; 26 = surstylus, broadest (sublateral-subventral) view; 27 = postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. 28–29: female: 28 = spermathecae; 29 = cerci, dorsal view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 24; 0.2 mm for Fig. 21; 0.1 mm for Figs 22–23, 25–29" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946037/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
), neck of spermathecae without warts.
</paragraph>
